+/*
+ * Migrator-side override of upstream BLACS ``dgsum2d_.c``.
+ *
+ * Differs from upstream in the default-topology (``ttop == ' '``) path
+ * only: the original calls ``MPI_Reduce`` / ``MPI_Allreduce`` with the
+ * stock ``MPI_SUM`` op on whatever ``bp->dtype`` happens to be — which
+ * the migrator rewrites to ``MPI_REAL16`` (kind16) or
+ * ``MPI_LONG_DOUBLE`` (kind10). Intel MPI 2021.17 does not implement
+ * ``MPI_SUM`` correctly on either of those datatypes (segfaults inside
+ * ``MPIR_SUM`` on REAL16; returns nonsense on LONG_DOUBLE). MPICH's
+ * ``mpiexec`` instead deadlocks rank 0 at 100% CPU — different failure
+ * mode, same gap.
+ *
+ * The fix mirrors upstream ``zgsum2d_.c``: register a user-defined
+ * combine op via ``MPI_Op_create(BI_dMPI_sum, ...)`` that calls
+ * ``BI_dvvsum`` (the same vector-sum kernel used by every other
+ * topology branch in this routine). After migration the q/e/m clones
+ * call ``BI_qMPI_sum``/``BI_eMPI_sum``/``BI_mMPI_sum`` which dispatch
+ * to ``BI_qvvsum``/``BI_evvsum``/``BI_mvvsum`` — those are already
+ * generated correctly by the BLACS C migrator from ``BI_dvvsum.c`` and
+ * use the target's native ``+=`` operator on the precision-promoted
+ * scalar type.
+ *
+ * No quad-MPI helper or runtime registration is needed — the user-op
+ * is created and freed per call, exactly like the existing complex
+ * ``zgsum2d_`` path. The companion ``BI_dMPI_sum.c`` ships alongside
+ * this file via the same ``source_overrides`` recipe entry.
+ *
+ * See the B01 description in recipes/blacs.yaml for full context.
+ */
+
 #include "Bdef.h"
 
 
